<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-15T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4465: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurnum</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-15T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>147. Your 260 June 13, 7 p.m.</p>
                        <p>You should avoid if possible raising question of recognition since, as
                            stated by you, the change is of administration rather than of
                            government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>